<%- include('partials/nav') %>
<main class="container prose">
  <h1>Tutorial &amp; Setup</h1>

  <h2>1. Create a Cloudflare API Token</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Go to <strong>Cloudflare Dashboard → My Profile → API Tokens → Create Token</strong>.</li>
    <li>Use a custom token with these permissions:
      <ul>
        <li><code>Zone → Zone → Read</code></li>
        <li><code>Zone → Ruleset → Edit</code></li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Scope it to the specific zones you'll use, then create and copy the token.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>2. Connect the token</h2>
  <p>Paste it on the <a href="/domains">Domains</a> page. The Master performs a
     dry-run to confirm the scopes before storing it (encrypted).</p>

  <h2>3. Register &amp; activate a domain</h2>
  <p>Pick a zone, register it (max 10), then activate it (max 5 active). Activation
     provisions the redirect ruleset on Cloudflare.</p>

  <h2>4. Create short URLs</h2>
  <p>Add URLs singly or in bulk. Each request is queued on the Master; the
     background worker writes the 302 redirect rule to Cloudflare. Status moves
     from <em>queued → active</em>.</p>

  <h2>5. Sync / Rebuild</h2>
  <p>If Cloudflare and the panel disagree, use <strong>Rebuild</strong> on the
     domain to rewrite all rules from the system of record.</p>

  <p class="muted">See also the <a href="/agreement">User Agreement / TOS</a>.</p>
</main>
<%- include('partials/foot') %>
